38 //
39 // Base class for all environment models, providing separate collision check
40 // functions for each type of tracking error bound. All environments are
41 // boxes in 3D space. Environment is templated on the specific type of sensor
42 // message (M) which may be generated from or incpororated into a derived class,
43 // and sensor parameters (P) which may be used to generate sensor readings.
44 //
46

48 #define FASTRACK_ENVIRONMENT_ENVIRONMENT_H

60 using bound::Box;

62 template<typename M, typename P>
63 class Environment {
64 public:
65  virtual ~Environment() {}
66 
67  // Initialize from a ROS NodeHandle.
68  bool Initialize(const ros::NodeHandle& n);
69 
70  // Derived classes must provide a collision checker which returns true if
71  // and only if the provided position is a valid collision-free configuration.
72  // Provide a separate collision check for each type of tracking error bound.
73  virtual bool IsValid(const Vector3d& position, const Box& bound) const = 0;
74 
75  // Utility for checking multiple positions.
76  bool AreValid(const std::vector<Vector3d>& positions, const Box& bound) const;
77 
78  // Generate a sensor measurement.
79  virtual M SimulateSensor(const P& params) const = 0;
80 
81  // Derived classes must have some sort of visualization through RViz.
82  virtual void Visualize() const = 0;
83 
84 protected:
85  explicit Environment()
86  : initialized_(false) {}
87 
88  // Load parameters. This may be overridden by derived classes if needed
89  // (they should still call this one via Environment::LoadParameters).
90  virtual bool LoadParameters(const ros::NodeHandle& n);
91 
92  // Register callbacks.
93  bool RegisterCallbacks(const ros::NodeHandle& n);
94 
95  // Update this environment with the information contained in the given
96  // sensor measurement.
97  // NOTE! This function needs to publish on `updated_topic_`.
98  virtual void SensorCallback(const typename M::ConstPtr& msg) = 0;
99 
100  // Upper and lower bounds.
101  Vector3d lower_;
102  Vector3d upper_;
103 
104  // Publishers and subscribers.
105  ros::Publisher vis_pub_;
106  ros::Publisher updated_pub_;
107  ros::Subscriber sensor_sub_;
108 
109  std::string vis_topic_;
110  std::string updated_topic_;
111  std::string sensor_topic_;
112 
113  // Frame in which to publish visualization.
114  std::string fixed_frame_;
115 
116  // Naming and initialization.
117  std::string name_;
118  bool initialized_;
119 }; //\class Environment

123 // Initialize from a ROS NodeHandle.
124 template<typename M, typename P>
125 bool Environment<M, P>::Initialize(const ros::NodeHandle& n) {
126  name_ = ros::names::append(n.getNamespace(), "Environment");
127 
128  if (!LoadParameters(n)) {
129  ROS_ERROR("%s: Failed to load parameters.", name_.c_str());
130  return false;
131  }
132 
133  if (!RegisterCallbacks(n)) {
134  ROS_ERROR("%s: Failed to register callbacks.", name_.c_str());
135  return false;
136  }
137 
138  // Visualize.
139  Visualize();
140 
141  initialized_ = true;
142  return true;
143 }
144 
145 // Load parameters. This may be overridden by derived classes if needed
146 // (they should still call this one via Environment::LoadParameters).
147 template<typename M, typename P>
148 bool Environment<M, P>::LoadParameters(const ros::NodeHandle& n) {
149  ros::NodeHandle nl(n);
150 
151  // Sensor topic/service.
152  if (!nl.getParam("topic/sensor_sub", sensor_topic_)) return false;
153  if (!nl.getParam("topic/updated_env", updated_topic_)) return false;
154  if (!nl.getParam("vis/env", vis_topic_)) return false;
155 
156  // Frame of reference to publish visualization in.
157  if (!nl.getParam("frame/fixed", fixed_frame_)) return false;
158 
159  // Upper and lower bounds of the environment.
160  if (!nl.getParam("env/upper/x", upper_(0))) return false;
161  if (!nl.getParam("env/upper/y", upper_(1))) return false;
162  if (!nl.getParam("env/upper/z", upper_(2))) return false;
163 
164  if (!nl.getParam("env/lower/x", lower_(0))) return false;
165  if (!nl.getParam("env/lower/y", lower_(1))) return false;
166  if (!nl.getParam("env/lower/z", lower_(2))) return false;
167 
168  return true;
169 }
170 
171 // Register callbacks.
172 template<typename M, typename P>
173 bool Environment<M, P>::RegisterCallbacks(const ros::NodeHandle& n) {
174  ros::NodeHandle nl(n);
175 
176  // Subscribers.
177  sensor_sub_ = nl.subscribe(
178  sensor_topic_.c_str(), 1, &Environment<M, P>::SensorCallback, this);
179 
180  // Publishers.
181  vis_pub_ = nl.advertise<visualization_msgs::Marker>(
182  vis_topic_.c_str(), 1, false);
183 
184  updated_pub_ = nl.advertise<std_msgs::Empty>(
185  updated_topic_.c_str(), 1, false);
186 
187  return true;
188 }
189 
190 // Provide auxiliary validity checkers for sets of positions.
191 template<typename M, typename P>
192 bool Environment<M, P>::AreValid(
193  const std::vector<Vector3d>& positions, const Box& bound) const {
194  // Return Boolean AND of all IsValid calls.
195  for (const auto& p : positions) {
196  if (!IsValid(p, bound))
197  return false;
198  }
199 
200  return true;
201 }
